faultDetection.description: If set to True, the output will include an additional column flagging the observations considered as abnormal

averageTemp.description: Name of the column containing the average temperature (optional, if provided sampling should be daily)

datetime.description: Name of the column containing the datetime (sampling should be daily)

dayGroups.description: Name of the column containing day groups (optional)

degreeDaysMethod.description: The method used to compute degree days from daily Temperature statistics. 'best' will select the best choice as appropriate

drivers.description: List of column names, containing drivers that may influence the building's energy consumption (optional, if sampling is daily these are typically process-related information; if sampling is weekly or monthly, these can contain degree-days; in which case do not provide temperature-related columns)

improveCalendar.description: If 'None', the component will create one submodel per day group provided in the input data, if any, or create a single model with all samples if no day group is provided. If 'fast', 'medium' or 'full', the component will try to merge day groups found to have similar behaviour, in the same submodel. This search for calendar improvements takes time so three strategies are proposed according to their speed.

localTimeZone.description: Name of the local timezone, Olson format

maxNbMergedDayGroups.description: Maximum number of merged day groups that can be created by the component when it tries to improve the calendar.

maxTemp.description: Name of the column containing the maximum temperature (optional, if provided a maxTemp temperature should also be provided, and sampling should be daily)

minTemp.description: Name of the column containing the minimum temperature (optional, if provided a maxTemp temperature should also be provided, and sampling should be daily)

outliersDetectionNbSigma.description: The number of standard deviation used as threshold to detect outliers. A sample will be considered an outlier if it is "too far" from the robust model prediction ; the "too far" threshold is determined with this parameter. A higher value will remove less outliers.

positiveDrivers.description: List of drivers with a positive influence on energy consumption

robustnessMode.description: Sets the trade-off between accuracy and running time

signatureType.description: Model shape desired for the regression

target.description: Name of the column containing the building energy consumption.

modelID.description: Represents the identification of the created model, which is securely stored on the Schneider Electric platform. This ID can be used to retrieve the model created in the `createModel` service.
